div.p:
To Play ſometimes, to divert ones ſelf; or entertain civil Company, is not ſo much to be diſallowed;
but to do it ſo often, as to be called a Gameſter, is to be avoided; for then it looks more like Buſineſs than a Recreation; for it hath Conſequences of ſeveral kinds, not to be endured. It will engage you into a habit of Idleneſs, and ill Hours, draw you unto ill mixed Company, make you ne •
lect your Affairs abroad and at home.
